<section xml:id="sec-appA-substitution-and-integration-by-parts" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Substitution and integration by parts</title>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-appA-subs-substitution">
    <title>Substitution</title>

    <p>Substitution reverses the chain rule.</p>

    <p>
      If
      <md>u=g(x),</md>
      then
      <md>\boxed{du=g'(x)\,dx.}</md>
      <md>\boxed{\int f(g(x))g'(x)\,dx=\int f(u)\,du.}</md>
      For definite integrals,
      <md>\boxed{\int_a^b f(g(x))g'(x)\,dx=\int_{g(a)}^{g(b)} f(u)\,du.}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-appA-subs-substitution-checklist">
    <title>Substitution checklist</title>

    <p>
      <md>
        <mrow>1.\amp \text{Choose }u=g(x).</mrow>
        <mrow>2.\amp \text{Compute }du=g'(x)\,dx.</mrow>
        <mrow>3.\amp \text{Replace the integrand and differential.}</mrow>
        <mrow>4.\amp \text{For definite integrals, change the limits.}</mrow>
        <mrow>5.\amp \text{For indefinite integrals, substitute back to }x.</mrow>
      </md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-appA-subs-common-substitution-patterns">
    <title>Common substitution patterns</title>

    <p>
      <md>\int f(ax+b)\,dx\quad\text{use}\quad u=ax+b.</md>
      <md>\int f(x^2)\,2x\,dx\quad\text{use}\quad u=x^2.</md>
      <md>\int f(\sin x)\cos x\,dx\quad\text{use}\quad u=\sin x.</md>
      <md>\int f(\cos x)(-\sin x)\,dx\quad\text{use}\quad u=\cos x.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-appA-subs-warning-substitution">
    <title>Warning</title>

    <p>
      The substitution
      <md>u=g(x)</md>
      requires the matching factor
      <md>g'(x)\,dx.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      For example,
      <md>\int 2x e^{x^2}\,dx</md>
      is directly handled by <m>u=x^2</m>, but
      <md>\int e^{x^2}\,dx</md>
      is not.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-appA-subs-integration-by-parts">
    <title>Integration by parts</title>

    <p>Integration by parts reverses the product rule.</p>

    <p>
      <md>\boxed{\int u\,dv=uv-\int v\,du.}</md>
      For definite integrals,
      <md>\boxed{\int_a^b u\,dv=\left[uv\right]_a^b-\int_a^b v\,du.}</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-appA-subs-useful-choices">
    <title>Useful choices</title>

    <p>
      For
      <md>\int x e^x\,dx,</md>
      take
      <md>u=x,\qquad dv=e^x\,dx.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      For
      <md>\int x\cos x\,dx,</md>
      take
      <md>u=x,\qquad dv=\cos x\,dx.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      For
      <md>\int \ln x\,dx,</md>
      take
      <md>u=\ln x,\qquad dv=dx.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-appA-subs-warning-integration-by-parts">
    <title>Warning</title>

    <p>
      Integration by parts creates a boundary term:
      <md>[uv]_a^b.</md>
      Do not drop it.
    </p>
  </subsection>
</section>
